  "prompt": "Do NBA teams have captains?",
  "response": "Yes, NBA teams can have captains. While it's not a formal requirement by the league, many teams designate one or more players as captains to provide leadership both on and off the court. The captain(s) often serve as a liaison between the players and the coaching staff, help motivate their teammates, and represent the team during discussions with referees. The specifics of the role and the process for selecting captains may vary from team to team.",
